WEBVTT

00:14.480 --> 00:15.840
CHAPTER XIX

00:16.660 --> 00:21.500
And after these things I heard a great voice of much people in heaven, saying,

00:23.080 --> 00:28.880
Alleluia! Salvation and glory and honour and power unto the Lord our God!

00:29.300 --> 00:36.820
For true and righteous are His judgments, for He hath judged the great whore which did corrupt the earth with her fornication,

00:37.100 --> 00:40.540
and hath avenged the blood of His servants at her hand.

00:41.460 --> 00:42.740
And again they said,

00:43.840 --> 00:47.940
Alleluia! And her smoke rose up for ever and ever!

00:47.940 --> 00:56.080
And the four and twenty elders and the four beasts fell down and worshipped God that sat on the throne, saying,

00:57.240 --> 01:03.140
Amen! Alleluia! And a voice came out of the throne, saying,

01:03.940 --> 01:09.660
Praise our God, all ye His servants, and ye that fear Him both small and great!

01:09.660 --> 01:18.620
And I heard as it were the voice of a great multitude, and as the voice of many waters, and as the voice of mighty thunderings, saying,

01:20.520 --> 01:30.160
Alleluia! For the Lord God omnipotent reigneth! Let us be glad and rejoice and give honour to Him, for the marriage of the Lamb is come,

01:30.380 --> 01:38.060
and His wife hath made herself ready, and to her was granted that she should be arrayed in fine linen, clean and white.

01:38.060 --> 01:41.760
For the fine linen is the righteousness of saints.

01:42.320 --> 01:49.060
And He saith unto me, Right, blessed are they which are called unto the marriage supper of the Lamb!

01:49.620 --> 01:54.120
And He saith unto me, These are the true sayings of God!

01:54.680 --> 01:58.960
And I fell at His feet to worship Him, and He said unto me,

01:58.960 --> 02:06.540
See thou, do it not! I am thy fellow-servant, and of thy brethren that have the testimony of Jesus!

02:07.160 --> 02:11.980
Worship God, for the testimony of Jesus is the spirit of prophecy!

02:13.000 --> 02:17.920
And I saw heaven opened, and behold, a white horse!

02:18.360 --> 02:25.660
And He that sat upon Him was called Faithful and True, and in righteousness He doth judge and make war.

02:25.660 --> 02:35.060
His eyes were as a flame of fire, and on His head were many crowns, and He had a name written that no man knew but He Himself.

02:35.660 --> 02:43.480
And He was clothed with a vesture dipped in blood, and His name is called the Word of God.

02:44.000 --> 02:50.580
And the armies which were in heaven followed Him upon white horses, clothed in fine linen, white and clean.

02:50.580 --> 02:59.500
And out of His mouth goeth a sharp sword, that with it He should smite the nations, and He shall rule them with a rod of iron.

02:59.900 --> 03:04.580
And He treadeth the winepress of the fierceness and wrath of Almighty God.

03:05.100 --> 03:13.540
And He hath on His vesture and on His thigh a name written, King of Kings and Lord of Lords.

03:14.440 --> 03:23.120
And I saw an angel standing in the sun, and He cried with a loud voice, saying to all the fowls that fly in the midst of heaven,

03:24.020 --> 03:33.320
Come and gather yourselves together unto the supper of the great God, that ye may eat the flesh of kings, and the flesh of captains,

03:33.360 --> 03:43.020
and the flesh of mighty men, and the flesh of horses, and of them that sit on them, and the flesh of all men, both free and bond, both small and great.

03:43.640 --> 03:52.620
And I saw the beast, and the kings of the earth and their armies gathered together to make war against Him that sat on the horse, and against His army.

03:53.040 --> 04:01.640
And the beast was taken, and with Him the false prophet that wrought miracles before Him, with which He deceived them that had received the mark of the beast,

04:01.860 --> 04:03.780
and them that worshipped His image.

04:03.780 --> 04:13.100
These both were cast alive into a lake of fire burning with brimstone, and the remnant were slain with the sword of Him that sat upon the horse,

04:13.480 --> 04:18.840
which sword proceeded out of His mouth, and all the fowls were filled with their flesh.

